<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued June 15 at 8:17PM CDT until June 16 at 2:00AM CDT by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 845 PM CDT
FOR SOUTHWESTERN PIKE COUNTY...
At 817 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles southwest of
Antioch, or 7 miles south of Troy, moving west at 15 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Troy, Goshen, Antioch, Tarentum, Springhill, Mossy Grove and
Henderson.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
